{"_record_type": "fragment", "type": "expert_knowledge", "content": "# Q: Plan Mode: Incorrectly denying write_file to designated plans directory\n**Source:** https://github.com/google-gemini/gemini-cli/issues/23777\n\n## The Problem / Request\n### What happened?\nIn **Plan Mode**, the CLI incorrectly denies `write_file` calls to the designated plans directory (`.gemini/plans/`), even when the file being written is a `.md` file. The system returns a policy violation error stating that only `.md` files in the plans directory are allowed, which contradicts the actual operation being attempted.\n\n### What did you expect to happen?\nThe CLI should allow `write_file` and `replace` operations for `.md` files within the directory specified in `.gemini/settings.json` (under `general.plan.directory`) while in Plan Mode.\n\n### Client information\n```text\nAbout Gemini CLI\nCLI Version                           0.35.0\nGit Commit                            9804bd696\nModel                                 Auto (Gemini 3)\nSandbox                               no sandbox\nOS                                    darwin\nAuth Method                           Signed in with Google (REDACTED)\nTier                                  Gemini Code Assist in Google One AI Pro\nIDE Client                            JetBrains IDE\n```\n**Platform:** macOS 26.3.1 (Darwin)\n\n### Login information\nSigned in with Google Account (Google One AI Pro / Gemini Code Assist tier).\n\n### Anything else we need to know?\n**Steps to Reproduce:**\n1. Ensure `.gemini/settings.json` has `general.plan.directory` set to `.gemini/plans`.\n2. Enter Plan Mode using `enter_plan_mode`.\n3. Call `write_file` with `file_path: \".gemini/plans/test-plan.md\"`.\n\n**Error Observed:**\n> `Tool execution denied by policy. You are in Plan Mode and cannot modify source code. You may ONLY use write_file or replace to save plans to the designated plans directory as .md files.`\n\n**Additional Context:**\n- The error persis